Why Python over Bash?
1. 🔹 Better for Complex Logic
Bash becomes messy with multiple conditions and loops
Python is clean and easy to read

👉 Example: Nested if-else is much simpler in Python

2. 🔹 Easy to Read & Maintain
Python syntax is human-friendly
Bash scripts become hard to understand as they grow

👉 In teams, Python is preferred for long-term projects

3. 🔹 Powerful Libraries
Python has built-in modules like:
os (system tasks)
sys (arguments)
json (API/log parsing)

👉 Bash has very limited built-in capabilities

4. 🔹 Better Error Handling
Python supports try-except
Bash error handling is basic and tricky

👉 Helps in writing reliable automation scripts

5. 🔹 Works Beyond Linux
Bash is mainly for Linux/Unix
Python works on:
Linux
Windows
Cloud platforms ☁️
6. 🔹 Used in DevOps Tools
Many tools are built using Python:
Ansible
AWS SDK (Boto3)
Automation scripts

👉 So learning Python helps you understand tools better



